AB  - The authors measured event-related potentials with a craving manipulation to 
      investigate the neural correlates of drug cue reactivity in 13 adolescents who 
      are cannabis dependent (CD; ages 14-17). The P300 responses to marijuana (MJ) 
      pictures (MJ-P300) and control pictures (C-P300) were assessed after handling 
      neutral objects and again after handling MJ paraphernalia (MJP). Self-reported 
